issue.title: Logs written by ILogger does not shown in Monitor tab.
issue.body:
I create an azure function(v2) from visual studio, it's blob trigger. And I use the ILogger to write logs to application insights.

The code in function.cs like below:

public static class Function1
    {
        [FunctionName("Function1")]
        public static void Run([BlobTrigger("f22/{name}", Connection = "AzureWebJobsStorage")]Stream myBlob, string name, ILogger log)
        {
            log.LogInformation($"C# Blob trigger function Processed blob\n Name:{name} \n Size: {myBlob.Length} Bytes !!!");
            log.LogTrace("this is a trace info from ilogger !!!");
            log.LogInformation("this is a information from ilogger!!!");
        }
    }

And after I publish it to azure, I add application insights ikey to the application settings and save it.

Then upload some files to azure blob, the function works and i can see the logs are shown on the azure function log console.

![log-console](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25738099/53547726-bd4ca600-3b6a-11e9-91d6-e49bee23739a.JPG)


But in the azure function Monitor tab, I cannot see the logs generated. 

![monitor-tab](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25738099/53547905-351ad080-3b6b-11e9-878b-508208d42fe2.JPG)


but I can find the logs in application insights portal via search.

![app-insights-search](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25738099/53547735-c473b400-3b6a-11e9-8191-ec87630e7ec5.JPG)
